# Fraud Detection using Transaction Behavior Analysis

## Problem
Identify suspicious transactions based on abnormal spending behavior.

## Approach
- Analyzed transaction amounts to detect unusual patterns
- Created threshold-based rule to flag high-value transactions
- Added behavioral condition (transaction time) to improve accuracy

## Result
- Initial suspicious cases: 97
- After refinement: 81
- Reduced unnecessary alerts by improving detection logic

## Tools Used
- Python
- Pandas
- Jupyter Notebook
